title.rendered: TNPL Starting from Tomorrow, Here all the details you want to know

content.rendered:
The sixth season of the Tamil Nadu Premier League will begin tomorrow, June 23, and will conclude on July 31. Eights teams will compete against one another in a round-robin style similar to that used in other leagues. Thus, without wasting any further second, lets deep dive into all match details such as how it will be broadcast, and streamed, where it will be played, when it will be played, etc.

Where can you watch every TNPL game?

Star Network will broadcast the 2022 Tamil Nadu Premier League. Star Sports 1 and Star Sports HD will be the channels (English). Tamil speakers and viewers can access it on Star Sports 1 Tamil.
Where can you watch every game of the Tamil Nadu Premier League 2022 live streaming?
All TNPL matches are available for live streaming through the Disney + Hot star app.

Venue and Timings

Tamil Nadu Premier league 2022 will have 4 venues in their list to conduct all the matches, all entirely in the state and are:

SNR College ground, Coimbatore

Indian Cement Company Ground, Tirunelveli.

NPR College ground, Dindigul

Salem Cricket Stadium, Salem

The sixth season of the eagerly anticipated Tamil Nadu Premier League 2022 will kick off tomorrow with Chepauk Super Gillies vs. Nellai Royal Kings going head-to-head.

It’s interesting to note that most matches will take place at around 7:15 in the evening, however some will also be seen at around 3:15 in the afternoon. Look down below.
